CatDescriptText: Related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 8, 1963, pg.7 reads: " Royalty and Court - A unique way of choosing a "King and Queen" at the D.I. ball came when names were drawn from a box and the persons were called to the front. Pictured front center, Mr. and Mrs. Leonard Walk, Mr. and Mrs. Marian Williams; Joe Knight, Mr. and Mrs. Sherman Robinson, Mr. and Mrs. James Spencer, Mr. and Mrs. William Douglass and Mr. and Mrs. Jerry McDaniels who are not shown in picture.  Mr. Walk is the owner of radio station WAMO. - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of couples, Mr. and Mrs. Leonard Walk, standing front center, also including Mr. and Mrs. Marian Williams; Joe Knight, Mr. and Mrs. Sherman Robinson, Mr. and Mrs. James Spencer, Mr. and Mrs. William Douglass and Mr. and Mrs. Jerry McDaniels, standing on steps outside Hotel Webster Hall for D.I. ball
